&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO WE ARE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Grey Health is the culmination of the rich legacies of two powerhouse brands —Grey and TANK. With borderless employees spread across 20 studios in 18 countries, we all work collaboratively with one mission in mind: to deliver famously effective ideas that drive business results for top tier clients in the health and wellness market. In 2023, Grey was named a Top 100 Most Loved Workplace and our agency network and The Grey Group, ranked in the top ten award winners at the Cannes Lions International Festival of Creativity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While TANK and Grey maintain their unique identities and market presence, they now benefit from shared resources and strategic direction that help us unlock new opportunities across the globe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POSITION OVERVIEW&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Does your portfolio stand out? Are you curious and passionate about ideas? Do you thrive in a creative and collaborative environment? If so, we’re looking for you!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As anArt Director, you will conceptualize ideas generally with a Copywriter. Reporting to the Creative Director, you will develop and realize your concepts, all within the marketing strategy and across traditional and digital mediums.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL BE DOING&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and develop original, effective and memorable ideas and campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take initiative in understanding all aspects of creative elements that go into executing an idea.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conceptualize and design campaign materials for client meetings:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess campaigns’ visual requirements;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce projects (digital, social, radio, TV, print);&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise and approve, in collaboration with the copywriter, each stage of the campaign at the visual level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring ideas to life with mastery of craft and keen attention to detail;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Occasionally lead pitch undertakings;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifying new creative opportunities within projects;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess the confidence to present and defend ideas internally and externally;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide work that is on strategy and reflects the brand, with minimum revisions required by the client&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in new business development;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand how advertising works to solve marketing problems;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess and develop a comprehensive vision (360 degrees) of the creative concept and ensure that all connected activities (digital, social, TV, radio and print) are consistent with the strategy;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with copywriters, graphic designers, illustrators, client services, respecting timing &amp;amp; budgets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE ARE LOOKING FOR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diploma in graphic design or in a relevant discipline;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 3 years of experience in a similar position within an advertising agency;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Healthcare agency experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Client-focused, marked creative sensibility;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid interpersonal skills, strong and enthusiastic presenter;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to influence others, highly collaborative;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to manage multiple projects at once;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capable to work under pressure and able to work independently;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in MS Office 365 and Adobe Creative Suite (Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign);&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Adobe XD, Figma and Sketch, an asset;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE HAVE TO OFFER:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Challenging Work -&lt;/strong&gt

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO WE ARE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Grey Health is the culmination of the rich legacies of two powerhouse brands —Grey and TANK. With borderless employees spread across 20 studios in 18 countries, we all work collaboratively with one mission in mind: to deliver famously effective ideas that drive business results for top tier clients in the health and wellness market. In 2023, Grey was named a Top 100 Most Loved Workplace and our agency network and The Grey Group, ranked in the top ten award winners at the Cannes Lions International Festival of Creativity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While TANK and Grey maintain their unique identities and market presence, they now benefit from shared resources and strategic direction that help us unlock new opportunities across the globe.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POSITION OVERVIEW&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Associate Creative Director, you will play a pivotal role in leading the creative team to develop impactful and strategic campaigns that effectively communicate healthcare-related messages to target audiences. You will be responsible for combining your creative vision with your in-depth understanding of healthcare nuances to deliver compelling and compliant campaigns. Collaboration with cross-functional teams, including Creative Directors, Copywriters, Designers, Strategists, Account Managers, and clients, will be essential to ensure the successful execution of projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Associate Creative Director, Copy, will approach every brief with fresh eyes. You will create and inspire work that is superior across all channels, is distinctive, and is famously effective. With a background in copywriting, you will help set creative direction and offer hands-on guidance throughout client team projects, while displaying a cohesive understanding of brand requirements and key market factors. You will execute copy at the highest level, and help team members bring forward their best work, on-time and on-brief.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU’LL BE DOING:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrating comprehensive knowledge of each client’s brand and the overall healthcare industry by taking a lead role in the briefing, concepting, copy development, and execution of cross-channel initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evidencing a deep understanding of healthcare regulations, terminology, and trends to ensure all creative work meets industry-specific compliance standards while remaining compelling to the target audience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspiring copy and creative direction while providing ‘hands on’ support to the creative team and maintaining an advisory role throughout all projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Displaying highly advanced writing skills in the healthcare space, to effectively present a point of view, using logic, facts (medical and otherwise), and crafting a compelling storyline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Researching and developing new tone-of-voice guidelines for brands, as well as writing comprehensive guidelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with our Strategy and Account teams to ensure briefs are clear, insightful, and will inspire great creative development. Immersing yourself into the brand strategy and carry it through to the work, so that all of our communications can be smart and effective&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participating and/or leading client meetings/presentations and developing client relationships, while stewarding excellent work to market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE ARE LOOKING FOR: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 7+ years of industry experience in a well-established, creative role with a proven track record&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Agency experience working across all channels&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong creative portfolio highlighting relevant/category experience, particularly in healthcare

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO WE ARE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Grey Health is the culmination of the rich legacies of two powerhouse brands —Grey and TANK. With borderless employees spread across 20 studios in 18 countries, we all work collaboratively with one mission in mind: to deliver famously effective ideas that drive business results for top tier clients in the health and wellness market. In 2023, Grey was named a Top 100 Most Loved Workplace and our agency network and The Grey Group, ranked in the top ten award winners at the Cannes Lions International Festival of Creativity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While TANK and Grey maintain their unique identities and market presence, they now benefit from shared resources and strategic direction that help us unlock new opportunities across the globe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POSITION OVERVIEW&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Associate Project Manager has the primary responsibility to coordinate the execution of all projects (TV, Digital, Print, Mobile, etc.) for all assigned brands. This position is the hub of communication for the team regarding all project deliverables. It requires great attention to detail, excellent communication, organizational and multitasking skills.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On any given day you can expect to:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the development and tracking of integrated project plans alongside Senior Project Managers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adapt and apply the delivery approach to meet project objectives and client business drivers with ownership of project communications.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare submissions for projects.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in project estimations, facilitate the development of project deliverables, and maintain processes to manage scope throughout the project lifecycle.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop timelines with input from relevant departments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Update timelines based on client and/or internal changes, keeping accurate timelines throughout the life of the job.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remind team members of upcoming due dates and alert the key partners should&amp;nbsp;dates shift&amp;nbsp;along the life cycle of the task.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review weekly estimates v. actuals and submit accurate timesheets&amp;nbsp;daily.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and run weekly status&amp;nbsp;meeting&amp;nbsp;and provide day-to-day project status to the team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU WILL NEED&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven project management, time management, organization, and prioritization skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational skills, attention to detail, and the ability to efficiently handle multiple tasks&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High level of language and communication skills as well as an interest in high science&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-3 years’ experience within Advertising&amp;nbsp;or related industry&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO YOU ARE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creative: Putting together two things to create a third thing no one’s ever seen before&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Productive: Acting on ideas to make things happen and get stuff done&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative: Focused on the greater good versus personal gain&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adaptable: Ready and able to embrace change&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE HAVE TO OFFER&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Challenging Work -&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;As leaders in the health advertising industry, we thrive on solving complex problems and innovation. Each employee is encouraged to bring their best

&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;En tant que Directeur(trice) artistique, tu travailleras en étroite collaboration avec les Concepteurs-rédacteurs pour développer, concevoir et exécuter des concepts et des mises en page innovants pour des campagnes publicitaires multicanales. Ton travail donnera vie aux messages des clients de façon persuasive et inattendue, en garantissant des solutions créatives percutantes qui résonnent auprès des audiences. Relevant de l’ACD, tu joueras un rôle clé dans la création d’expériences de marque mémorables. En rejoignant notre studio de Montréal tu feras partie d’une équipe créative à l’esprit international, entourée de certains des esprits les plus brillants de leur domaine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p3&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TES RESPONSABILITÉS PRINCIPALES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;ul1&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;Collaborer avec le Concepteur-rédacteur pour assurer une parfaite synergie entre le texte et le visuel, afin d’atteindre nos standards « Famously Effective ».&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;Recevoir et mettre en œuvre les commentaires des directeurs créatifs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;Communiquer régulièrement avec les équipes Service-conseil, Stratégie, Gestion de projet et Production afin de garantir le respect des livrables et des échéances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;Travailler sur une variété de projets déployés sur plusieurs canaux.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;Soutenir les équipes à travers toutes les phases du projet, de l’idéation à la production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;Aider les responsables créatifs lors des présentations et livrables clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;Te tenir informé(e) des dernières tendances créatives mondiales : festivals, études de cas, maisons de production et meilleures créations de l’industrie. Comprendre ce qui t’inspire et ce qu’il faut pour y arriver te permettra de créer du travail qui inspire les autres.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;Rester à jour sur les dernières avancées technologiques (logiciels de design, outils numériques, plateformes) pour améliorer les processus créatifs et livrer des solutions innovantes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;Être curieux(se) des tendances culturelles, des médias sociaux et des comportements de ton audience pour intégrer des éléments pertinents dans les briefs et campagnes. Amener le monde extérieur dans notre travail afin que nos marques puissent participer à la conversation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p3&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CE QUE NOUS RECHERCHONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;ul1&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;2 à 3 ans (ou plus) d’expérience dans un rôle créatif bien établi, avec un parcours démontré.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;Expérience sur tous les canaux.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;Portfolio créatif solide, mettant en valeur une expérience pertinente (catégorie/secteur).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;Solides compétences de communication verbale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;Excellentes compétences rédactionnelles et de présentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;Capacité à gérer plusieurs projets dans un environnement rapide et exigeant.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;Maîtrise de la suite Adobe, des outils d’IA ou d’autres outils similaires.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p3&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUI TU ES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;ul1&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Créatif(ve)&lt;/strong&gt; : tu sais assembler deux choses pour en créer une troisième, inédite.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;li1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conceptuel(le)&lt;/strong&gt; : tu transformes les idées en actions concrètes.&lt;/li&gt;
